content:
Package External Client Apps In Second-Generation Managed Packages

Take advantage of the external client apps framework. The new and improved generation of connected apps is catching up to connected apps fast. The new framework now supports headless login, passwordless login, and guest user flows using the Authorization Code and Credentials Flow. You can also configure an external client app to issue JSON Web Token (JWT)-based access tokens, which is required for the guest user flow. External client apps can be included in second-generation managed packages.

Where: This change applies to second-generation managed packages.
